RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Maiden Claiming Purse 27000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUN BAMBI RUN raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn still in the two path, challenged entering stretch and dueled in the lane, pulling clear late. REAUX BINA hit the gate leaving it, saved ground around the first bend, raced off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the rail coming around the second bend and dueled to the finish, getting caught near the wire. SURREY chased the pace setter on the inside through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn tin in the two path and dueled to the wire, getting caught late and just missing second. DESTINY'S GRACE raced in the four path early, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the three path and finished evenly. BOLD EXAGGERATION hit the gate at the break, raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three path and was outkicked in the lane. ADAYINSPAIN saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and tired in the stretch. IRISH MOLLY raced into traffic and steadied while saving ground around the first turn, raced in the middle of the pack heading into the backstretch, dropped back to trail the field around the second bend and was empty in the stretch while drifiting out. THE RIDER OF HORSE ONE, IRISH MOLLY, CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE THREE, ADAYINSPAIN, CITING INTERFERENCE HEADED INTO THE FIRST TURN. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

OLD SCHOOL FLASH raced in the two path headed into the first bend, bumping with MAVE RUNNER in the process, chased the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and kept on in the lane. SHEZA CAT raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and was outkicked in the lane. UPON REVIEW, HORSE FIVE, LEPRECHAUN CHARM, WAS DETERMINED NOT TO HAVE A HAD A FAIR BEGINNING AND WAS DECLARED A NON STARTER BY THE STEWARDS. NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH REGARDING THAT INCIDENT.
